02/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Solomon Passy and his visiting Spanish counterpart, Ana de Palacio, said on Monday (1 September) the two governments were co-operating in the preparation of a new UN Security Council resolution on Iraq. 
The document would include additional countries in the post-war reconstruction process and would seek broader involvement by NATO and the EU in the process.
In other news Monday, the chambers of commerce of Bulgaria and Russia signed a co-operation agreement that envisions the development of bilateral relations in the areas of investment, information exchange, and co-operation between small and medium-sized businesses, among other things. 
(Trud, Dnevnik, 24 Chassa, Sega - 02/09/03; BTA, BNR, BNT - 01/09/03)
